# make file set env variables


+make +makefile +gnu +gnumake


/Users/michal/Documents/journal/zettel/20220824135819-makefile-usage-guide


The basic way to do this is through this kind of directive towards the top of
the Makefile file.

```makefile
export CGO_ENABLED = 1
```

Each recipe in make is invoked in a separate subshell unless .ONESHELL target
is in effect (it works with GNU make >= 3.82)
